quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,46,"And we used to deny the Day of Recompense"
  74,47,"Until there came to us the certainty [i.e., death]."
  74,48,"So there will not benefit them the intercession of [any] intercessors."
  77,34,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,35,"This is a Day they will not speak,"
  77,36,"Nor will it be permitted for them to make an excuse."
  78,31,"Indeed, for the righteous is attainment{1} -",footnotes:1:Of security, success and reward, including escape and safety from Hell.
  78,32,"Gardens and grapevines."
  78,33,"And full-breasted [companions] of equal age."
  79,25,"So Allāh seized him in exemplary punishment for the last and the first [transgression].{1}.",footnotes:1:i.e., for Pharaoh's setting himself up as a deity and for his previous oppression of the people and denial of Moses.
  79,26,"Indeed in that is a lesson [i.e., warning] for whoever would fear [Allāh]."
  79,27,"Are you a more difficult creation or is the heaven? He [i.e., Allāh] constructed it."
  80,22,"Then when He wills, He will resurrect him."
  80,23,"No! He [i.e., man] has not yet accomplished what He commanded him."
  80,24,"Then let mankind look at his food -"
  81,19,"[That] indeed, it [i.e., the Qur’ān] is a word [conveyed by] a noble messenger [i.e., Gabriel]"
  81,20,"[Who is] possessed of power and with the Owner of the Throne, secure [in position],"
  81,21,"Obeyed there [in the heavens] and trustworthy."
  82,13,"Indeed, the righteous will be in pleasure,"
  82,14,"And indeed, the wicked will be in Hellfire."
  82,15,"They will [enter to] burn therein on the Day of Recompense,"
  83,10,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers,"
  83,11,"Who deny the Day of Recompense."
  83,12,"And none deny it except every sinful transgressor."
  84,7,"Then as for he who is given his record in his right hand,"
  84,8,"He will be judged with an easy account"
  84,9,"And return to his people in happiness."
  85,4,"Destroyed [i.e., cursed] were the companions of the trench{1}",footnotes:1:Or "May they be destroyed" or "cursed." The "companions of the trench" (or ditch) were agents of a tyrannical king who refused to allow his people to believe in Allāh. Their evil deed in obedience to their ruler earned for them the curse of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) .
  85,5,"[Containing] the fire full of fuel,"
  85,6,"When they were sitting near it."